-- Ellison Says Oracle Explored, Dropped Making Java Phone
-- B y   K a r e n   G u l l o
-- 2012-04-17T17:48:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/ellison-says-oracle-explored-dropped-making-java-mobile-phone.html
Oracle Corp. Chief Executive
Officer  Larry Ellison , testifying in a $1 billion lawsuit
against  Google Inc. (GOOG) , told a jury today that his company explored
and ultimately abandoned developing a mobile phone using the
Java programming language.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Gullo in San Francisco at 
 kgullo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
